value.title: Andrew Giuliani to meet with Trump before potential New York gubernatorial campaign
value.excerpt: Andrew Giuliani is set to meet with former President Trump next week in Florida as he mulls a gubernatorial bid in New York.

value.title: Biden aims to cement US credibility on climate and galvanize world leaders at virtual summit
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden's ability to galvanize global momentum faces its first major test this week when he convenes 40 of his foreign counterparts for talks on combating the climate crisis.

value.title: Biden briefed on ‘tragic’ police killing of Ma’Khia Bryant, White House says
value.excerpt: Ma’Khia, 16, shot dead by police in Columbus, Ohio on Tuesday, minutes before jury announced guilty verdict in Chauvin murder case

value.title: Biden adviser's brother lobbying White House for pharma giants, docs reveal
value.excerpt: Jeff Ricchetti began lobbying the White House at the beginning of this year’s first quarter, with disclosures showing that he was representing pharmaceutical giants Horizon Therapeutics, GlaxoSmithKline and Vaxart Inc., according to financial disclosure reports.

value.title: Boebert, Roy seek to force vote on reversing Biden's oil and gas executive orders
value.excerpt: Reps. Lauren Boebert and Chip Roy launched an effort Wednesday to force a House vote on reversing President Biden's oil and gas executive orders that the GOP lawmakers panned as detrimental to the economy and America's energy independence.

value.title: Andrew Giuliani to meet with Trump as he preps NY gubernatorial bid
value.excerpt: Andrew Giuliani, the son of former New York City Mayor Rudy Giuliani and a former public liaison official inside the Trump White House, will meet with the former President at Mar-a-Lago next week as he finalizes his plans to launch a campaign for New York governor.

value.title: 8 Podcasts to Help Make Sense of Post-Trump America
value.excerpt: In the wake of a most untraditional presidency, these shows will keep you up-to-date on what’s happening in Washington and our politically polarized country.

value.title: AP sources: Biden to pledge halving greenhouse gases by 2030
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden will pledge to cut U.S. greenhouse gas emissions at least in half by 2030 as he convenes a virtual climate summit with 40 world leaders

value.title: Biden ignores $1B in riot damage while praising George Floyd protesters after Chauvin conviction
value.excerpt: President Biden neglected to acknowledge the rioting, looting, arson and worse that reportedly caused more than $1 billion in property damage last year as he praised George Floyd protesters Tuesday following Derek Chauvin's conviction on murder charges.

value.title: Foxconn plant, once touted by Trump as a 13,000-job juggernaut, will now create just 1,500 jobs
value.excerpt: Taiwan electronics manufacturer Foxconn is drastically scaling back a planned $10 billion factory in Wisconsin, confirming its retreat from a project that former President Donald Trump once called "the eighth wonder of the world.

value.title: Leo Terrell: Biden, Democrats' reaction to Chauvin verdict shows 'you cannot satisfy these extremists'
value.excerpt: President Biden and his Democratic allies still want to make the Derek Chauvin trial about race relations in America, civil rights attorney Leo Terrell told "Hannity" Tuesday.

value.title: Foxconn mostly abandons $10 billion Wisconsin project touted by Trump

value.title: Biden, Harris slam 'systemic racism' in US, say Chauvin guilty verdict is 'giant step' toward racial justice
value.excerpt: The guilty verdict in the murder trial of former Minneapolis police Officer Derek Chauvin "can be a giant step forward in the march toward justice in America," President Biden and Vice President Harris said Tuesday.

value.title: Brian Sicknick death ruling debunks media narrative that fueled second Trump impeachment: Hurt
value.excerpt: The official ruling on the cause of U.S. Capitol Police officer Brian Sicknick's death debunks the media narrative upon which former President Donald Trump's second impeachment was largely predicated,

value.title: Biden DOJ dispatches 'peacemakers' to Minneapolis ahead of Chauvin verdict: report
value.excerpt: The Justice Department has reportedly dispatched officials from its Community Relations Service to act as peacemakers and facilitate listening sessions in Minneapolis.

value.title: Scalise accuses Biden administration of 'exempting' illegal immigrants from COVID-19 restrictions
value.excerpt: FIRST ON FOX: House Republican Whip Steve Scalise on Tuesday wrote to Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas, accusing the Biden administration of exempting illegal immigrants from COVID-19 restrictions – while citing testimony from Dr. Anthony Fauci to make his case.

value.title: Durbin wants more info on Trump appointees 'burrowed' into career Justice Dept. jobs
value.excerpt: The Illinois senator, citing NBC News' reporting, requested info on Trump appointees who landed career civil service jobs at the Executive Office of Immigration Review.

value.title: Steve Scalise Says Maxine Waters Wants 'Violent' Protests, Trump Urged Peaceful D.C. Rally
value.excerpt: "I haven't heard Maxine saying anything about people 'peacefully' protesting," said Louisiana GOP Rep. Scalise Tuesday.

value.title: Biden praying for 'right verdict' in Chauvin trial
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden says he is “praying the verdict is the right verdict” in the trial of former Minneapolis Police Officer Derek Chauvin and that he believes the case to be “overwhelming.”

value.title: Sikh Coalition urges Biden to appoint Sikh American liaison in wake of Indianapolis FedEx shooting
value.excerpt: In the wake of the FedEx shooting that left eight people dead, including four members of the Sikh community, the Sikh Coalition wants President Joe Biden’s administration to enact policies to address “long standing challenges” impacting Sikh Americans.

value.title: Watch Mike Lindell get tricked by a prank caller pretending to be Donald Trump during a livestream for his new social-media site
value.excerpt: MyPillow CEO Mike Lindell launched social-media site Frank on Monday with a 48-hour livestream that was plagued by technical issues and prank calls.

value.title: New Amy Klobuchar book attacks Trump for ‘a whole lot of bluster’ on antitrust
value.excerpt: Minnesota senator says ex-president never had any intention of reining in big companies for pursuing anti-competitive practices

value.title: Trump campaign chair on falling poll numbers, endorsing Paul Ryan
value.excerpt: Donald Trump's campaign is on the defensive after a week full of controversies, including his feud with the family of a fallen soldier and comments about sexual harassment in the workplace. Trump campaign chairman Paul Manafort joins "CBS This Morning" to discuss Trump's refusal to endorse House Speaker Paul Ryan in the Wisconsin primary race and Trump's falling poll numbers.

value.title: Trump says being president was 'very traumatic' but he 'loved doing it' because he 'helped people'
value.excerpt: "I had a great life, great company, great business, no problems," Trump told Fox News. "And now all I do is, people go after you. It's vicious."

value.title: Biden called George Floyd's brother as nation awaits verdict in Derek Chauvin trial
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden called George Floyd's brother Philonise Floyd on Monday as his family and the nation await a verdict in the trial of former Minneapolis police Officer Derek Chauvin.
